cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the user-interface design and how it affects users' ability to find interesting content on social media sites. This topic falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper analyzes the cognitive limitations of humans, which relates to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses how people divide their limited attention among competing sources of information, which is related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Software Development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of cybersecurity, as the user-interface design can mediate information spread, which falls under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
